Subject: rPSA-2008-0157-1 kernel

rPath Security Advisory: 2008-0157-1
Published: 2008-05-02
Products:
    rPath Linux 1

Rating: Severe
Exposure Level Classification:
    Local User Deterministic Privilege Escalation
Updated Versions:
    kernel=conary.rpath.com@rpl:1-vmware/2.6.24.6-0.1-1
    kernel=conary.rpath.com@rpl:1-xen/2.6.16.33-0.3-1
    kernel=conary.rpath.com@rpl:1/2.6.24.6-0.1-1

rPath Issue Tracking System:
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-2501

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-1375
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-1675

Description:
    Previous versions of the kernel package have multiple vulnerabilities
    resolved in this release.  The most severe could allow local users
    to cause a Denial of Service or possibly gain escalated privileges.
    
    A system reboot is required to resolve these issues.

http://wiki.rpath.com/Advisories:rPSA-2008-0157

